        "timestamp": "2020-05-12 18:13:41.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nMay be, but this resolves one of the issue with :ref: \"Installing or Upgrading Policy\" as a label used and we have a reference of it on the page. Which it wasn't picking without this.\n \nAs per  https://sublime-and-sphinx-guide.readthedocs.io/en/latest/references.html\nAllow reference sections using its title.\n\nI have tested it, a) it removed the warning. b)link become accessible on the page for \"Installing or Upgrading Policy\" referencing the section.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "b8b02224692313b35bc7570b773f0db6f91ac344",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1725,
          "name": "Utkarsh Jauhari",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "uj426b@att.com",
          "username": "uj426b"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2020-05-12 18:18:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> May be, but this resolves one of the issue with :ref: \"Installing or Upgrading Policy\" as a label used and we have a reference of it on the page. Which it wasn't picking without this.\n>  \n> As per  https://sublime-and-sphinx-guide.readthedocs.io/en/latest/references.html\n> Allow reference sections using its title.\n> \n> I have tested it, a) it removed the warning. b)link become accessible on the page for \"Installing or Upgrading Policy\" referencing the section.\n\nNow after this, Policy/engine left with 2 warnings, and both labels are same which needs a reference, which is missing on the page unlike above. So, we don't have that section on the page \"rebuilding and/or modifying the policy charts\"\nThink, may be we include the reference or we remove this label ?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
